on marks do not mean the same thing as they do in English. The apostrophe is used to indicate a glottal stop, while the colon means the same thing it does in IPA (vowel length)%0a%3c %0a%3c Sources:%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohawk_language%0a%3c https://www.ethnologue.com/about/language-status%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
